# 🕉️ VakyaLang Licensing

Copyright (c) 2026 Raj Mitra

This repository uses a **dual-license model** to ensure the integrity of the runtime while allowing open study of the language specification.

## 1. Runtime and Implementation
All source code for the runtime, compiler, interpreter, and execution engine (contained in `vak-lang/` and `sanskrit-coder/`) is licensed under:
**GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPLv3)**
Any modification or network deployment of this code must release its source code under the same license.

## 2. Language Specification and Documentation
All specifications, grammar definitions, and architectural documentation (contained in `docs/` and `spec/`) are licensed under:
**Apache License 2.0**
This allows researchers and developers to reference and cite the specification freely while providing patent protection.

## 3. Attribution Requirement
You may not use this project without proper attribution to the original author. You must retain all copyright notices in any redistributed or modified version.

